I came on game day and food was terrible service was great. I'm hoping it was just because of game day.  This was my top spot to get wings and recommend to many as the best in Iowa. I ordered the garlic jalapeno and it usually has small chunks of garlic and jalapeno in the sauce but it didn't this time disappointing but wasn't going to send them back. First wing was literally totally uncooked in the middle we are talking the color and texture of uncooked chicken. I sent them back and after a 25 min wait for replacement wings the sauce came back worse this time wasnt even mixed up but you think they would make sure they were cooked this time but they were not. I gave up on the wings at this point and tried my girlfriends reuben they she hadn't eaten much and I found out why. The reuben tasted like cornbeff hash out of a can and lacked sauerkraut.  I hope this was just a off day and rush because of game day I want my wing spot back. I will be back soon and hopefully you have your kitchen figured out. I will take this review down if you get your act together on the next trip, hopefully I can get my girlfriend to eat there again.

Five stars. Would give six if i could. This is my absolute favorite place in the world. My home and my escape from the real world. Donnelly’s is the most magical place in all existence and I have devoted my life to finding a better bar, and have failed.  This is it folks, the best of the best.  Staff = amazing. Booze = amazing. Food = amazing. Their kitchen manager, Dan, is the best chef in the entire world and if I become rich and famous I will force him to be my personal chef. The service is outstanding. Each and every one of their bartenders and servers are top notch. The only negative about this place is they got rid of the hot Thursday server. Heard she got a modeling gig in paris or is in a movie or something really cool.  Anyways, Donnelly’s is the best place on earth and if you’re not there yet stop reading, drop your phone, tablet, or computer, and go to Dons!

Every time I've gone here in the last six months, it's gotten worse and worse. Most of my favorite bartenders and servers have been replaced by rude, inattentive people. With the new ownership, at first they tried to save money by significantly cutting down on portion sizes (you'd get ten fries with fewer wings). They've recently come out with a new menu that is aesthetically awful, upped the prices, gotten rid of some Donnelly's favorites (sweet potato fries, fried mushrooms, creative seasonal cocktail specials). Incredibly disappointed that one of my 5+ year favorites in Iowa City has gone down the hole.

I don't normally feel obligated to speak out against organizations or social issues, but this time is different. Last Friday upon trying to enter Donnelly's one of my friends was cleared by the bouncer while the other was denied entrance simply due to his race. When confronting the bouncer and questioning how he could refuse someone due to race they received the answer "We can do whatever we want."  I was appalled that such behavior was taking place in Iowa City.  I for one will not be returning to Donnelly's anytime soon.

As a regular visitor to this establishment, all I have to say is how dare you. You have lost my business and many others. If you're looking for great Irish-American pub food, this downtown bar is definitely worth a visit. Donnelly's has the best Reuben in Iowa City, hands down. It's definitely in the top 3 I've had anywhere. And the prices are reasonable.  There are more exciting bars to visit in the downtown area, but for a quiet midday lunch with friends, this is a solid choice.  Not the most promising bar for meeting new people, but most certainly one of the better choices for starting the night off with those you already know.

The customer service in this restaurant is the worst we have experienced throughout. There are 2 waitresses who make you feel that you are a burden to them. They will ignore you to the fullest. We love the food at this pub and that is why we used to let go of the bad/ non-existent service, but not until last time's experience, when the treatment that we got from them is just unacceptable. The waitress would not come at first place, and the way they keep the food on the table is as if they were feeding us for free. We used to take our friends to this pub for the food that we love,  and even they got to experience the rudest waitresses ever. The treatment meted out to us at this place has annoyed us a lot and we have decided to stay away from them.

Great feel, vibe, and ambiance.  Friendly staff.  Awesome, awesome food.  Hand battered chicken, hand battered onion rings, sweet pot fries, best Reuben in town, deviled eggs and the deviled river contest, fish and chips mmm.  Wish they'd go back to peanuts instead of popcorn.  One of IC's gems!
